    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Local declarations can appear anywhere in your code, and do not have to be the first lines in a statement block.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Locals declared within a block are only visible inside that block.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">The VAR keyword has been added for ease of use, and because sometimes the type is difficult to specify, like in the area if LINQ or when anonymous types are used.</text></para>
